'''Digitron''' is a Croatian electronics company located in [[Buje]], [[Istria]]. Their name became eponymous for a handheld [[calculator]] in the former [[Yugoslavia|Yugoslav]] area. They are responsible for the release of Europe's first pocket calculator in 1971, called '''DB 800'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.epocalc.net/pages/calc_premieres|title=epocalc - Calculators|website=www.epocalc.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bturn.com/10124/geeks-behind-the-iron-curtain|title=Geeks behind the Iron Curtain: Yugoslav tech-socialism and the imaginary future - BTURN|website=bturn.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/40--rodendan-digitrona--u-bujama-je-izraden-prvi-europski-dzepni-kalkulator--te-1971-kostao-je-koliko-i-fico/954368/|title=U Bujama je izrađen prvi europski džepni kalkulator. Te 1971. koštao je koliko i fićo|publisher=}}</ref>
