iCOR is an education software which collects data for classroom observations.

== Classroom Observations ==

Classroom observations are a collection of lesson observations that is useful for teacher training and professional development.

=== Methodology in collection data ===

* form - a printed form is used to document and note various teacher practices 
* software app - a native app on a smart device may have a form with pre-populated drop-down lists, check boxes, radio buttons, comment areas that can be entered into the electronic form
* video - a video is recorded which shows various teacher practices

